another option which I use frequently is the Firefox browser plugin ereader. http://ebooks.stackexchange.com/users/230/julian Once the ebook is loaded you can then examine the DOM using Firebug. Of course this doesn't mean it will display the same issues you are trying to track down. The Nook uses the Adobe Digital Editions rendering engine.
If the CSS rules you are writing are not having any effect you could try adding the !important declaration at the end:
e.g p { margin:0!important; }

